  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Can you get my what's app account back on my phone?",
  "response": "To help you recover your WhatsApp account on your phone, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Ensure WhatsApp is Installed:**\n   - Check if WhatsApp is installed on your phone. If not, download it from the Google Play Store (for Android) or the App Store (for iOS).\n\n2. **Open WhatsApp:**\n   - Launch the WhatsApp application on your phone.\n\n3. **Verify Your Phone Number:**\n   - WhatsApp will ask you to enter your phone number. Make sure you enter the same phone number that was previously associated with your WhatsApp account.\n   - You will receive a verification code via SMS or a phone call. Enter the code in WhatsApp to verify your number.\n\n4. **Restore Your Chat History:**\n   - If you have backed up your chats to Google Drive (Android) or iCloud (iOS), WhatsApp will prompt you to restore your chat history after verifying your number. Follow the on-screen instructions to restore your chats.\n   - If you didn't back up your chats, unfortunately, you won't be able to recover your previous conversations.\n\n5. **Re-login to WhatsApp Web/Desktop:**\n   - If you use WhatsApp on your computer, you'll need to re-link your phone by scanning the QR code again.\n\nIf you're still having trouble, consider the following:\n\n- **Check Your Internet Connection:** Ensure your phone has a stable internet connection.\n- **Restart Your Phone:** Sometimes, a simple restart can resolve minor issues.\n- **Reinstall WhatsApp:** If the app is malfunctioning, uninstall and reinstall WhatsApp.\n- **Contact WhatsApp Support:** If none of the above steps work, you can contact WhatsApp support for further assistance.\n\nIf you need more specific help or run into any issues during these steps, please let me know!",
